blocks.text:
A quadratic form $q$ (equivalently its symmetric matrix $A$) is:
- **positive definite** if $q(v)>0$ for all $v\neq 0$;
- **negative definite** if $q(v)<0$ for all $v\neq 0$;
- **indefinite** if $q$ takes both positive and negative values;
- **positive (negative) semidefinite** if $q(v)\ge 0$ (resp. $\le 0$) for all $v$, with equality for some $v\neq 0$.

By the Spectral Theorem, $q$ is:
- **positive definite** $\iff$ all $\lambda_i>0$;
- **negative definite** $\iff$ all $\lambda_i<0$;
- **indefinite** $\iff$ there is a positive AND a negative eigenvalue;
- **positive semidefinite** $\iff$ all $\lambda_i\ge 0$ (with at least one $=0$); **negative semidefinite** $\iff$ all $\lambda_i\le 0$ (with at least one $=0$).
